snippet.textDisplay: A good friend of mine was in the marines back in like 87-88. Ended up  on Recon. Had set records in physical fitness during his bootcamp.  What's funny is  he was purely  like Rambo in my/ our eyes back then as he was ummmm special. ( I know not to say special forces). He  was Recon. He would never tell us pretty much anything he really did. He said he worked with dolphins though they were only good for a certain type of mission. He got injured and they told him he would never walk right again, WRONG--  he jumped many many times out of planes. he was one of the fastest ranking Marines. The thing is though. He never wanted to push that high. He wanted to stay in the field and he could have . He ended up running  some bases here in CA until he retired. He could have stayed in and gotten an even higher promotion. He straight up told us/ his friends he had accomplished everything he had ever wanted and that higher ranking was not what he was after. So he retired after 20 yrs in the Marines a while back now. I have so much respect for our Military men and women.  If you ever meet someone who was in the special forces-recon- seal- ect. Just thank them for protecting us. You have no idea what they do to keep our lives the way it is. Thank you ALL !!!!! God Bless America and GO RAIDERS!!!!!!
